  "blurb": "A four-bedroom villa set in forest within Kamala's Jomchang Estate on the Millionaire's Mile, its timber interiors and 15-metre infinity pool opening between green canopy and the Andaman Sea. Spa room, game room and beach access sit across some 2,200 m² on a 7,380 m² plot, with a four-strong team and a private chef, sleeping up to ten.",
  "detail": "Tucked into forest within the Jomchang Estate on Kamala's Millionaire's Mile, this four-bedroom villa trades the open cliff for something quieter — lush green canopy on one side, the vast Andaman Sea on the other, and a great deal of privacy in between. Warm timber interiors give it the feel of a refined cabin in the woods.\n\nA 15-metre infinity pool sits at the heart of the house, with living and dining spaces and an entertainment room opening around it. A master and three further en-suite bedrooms sleep up to ten across roughly 2,200 m² of building, on a wooded plot of some 7,380 m².\n\nThe villa is laid out for a relaxed group — a spa room with two massage beds and yoga mats, a game room with foosball and a library, table tennis, an outdoor BBQ, a sound system and five flatscreen televisions. Steps lead down toward beach access below the estate.\n\nA team of four, including a private chef, runs the day-to-day, with housekeeping, turndown, a guest concierge and return airport transfers included. The estate is gated with 24-hour security, minutes from Kamala's beach and west-coast restaurants.",
